West Street, north across Morris Street, showing the various buildings on the east side of this marginal thoroughfare. In the right background are the outstanding office structures constituting the City's famous skyline.

July 3, 1929
No's. 1-2-3

P. L. Sperr

44 and 45 (six-story white factory building, and 4-story one, adjoining it) West Street, east side, between Morris and Rector Streets, as seen across the clearance adjoining it which extends eastward from West to Washington Streets. Also shown, looking in a northeasterly direction, is the 35-story office building on the south side of Rector Street, from Washington to Greenwich Streets. In the right background is faintly visible the steeple of Trinity Church.
